Data Type : this specifies the type of data a particular variable holds

A) Primitive Data Types - 8 primitive data types
B) Non Primitive Data Types - Strings, Arrays etc.



Primitive Data Types :
======================


these are provided by java 


1)byte :   1 byte : -128 to 127  - can store whole numbers
2)Short :  2 bytes : -32,768 to 32,768- can store whole numbers
3)int : 4 bytes :  - can store whole numbers
4)long :  8 bytes - can store whole numbers
5)Float : 4 bytes :  - can store decimal numbers - 6 to 7 points
6)Double : 8 bytes :  - can store decimal numbers -15 points
7)char : 2 bytes - letters/alphabets
8)boolean : 1 bit - true and false;


Type casting : 

Widening :   assigning a smaller data type to larger data type 

ex : byte to int;

byte b = 10;

int i = b; 

Narrowing : assigning a larger data type  to smaller data type 

ex : int to byte

int i = 24;

byte b = (byte)i;

 